OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Richard
OL,4,CWillis
OL,6,F"We thought we must stay and do our
OL,7,Fstint. One chap trying to get the door
OL,8,Fopen in the process was killed. My
OL,9,Fonly duty was to tell the skipper on
OL,10,Fboard. He was shocked himself because
OL,11,Fof the noise.
OL,13,F"During that time the door became open
OL,14,Fenough to get the few tanks off."
OL,16,FMr Willis says the driver of a jeep
OL,17,Fthat was on board began to panic as
OL,18,Fthe door was being fixed and other
OL,19,Flanding craft had already offloaded
OL,20,Fvehicles.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
